        <title>Coding Style</title>
        <section ids="overview" names="overview">
            <title>Overview</title>
            <paragraph>Use these coding guidelines to ensure that your development complies with the project’s style and naming
                conventions.
                In general, follow the <reference name="Linux kernel coding style" refuri="https://kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html">Linux kernel coding style</reference>. Some coding rules follow AMD EC team.</paragraph>
            <target ids="linux-kernel-coding-style" names="linux\ kernel\ coding\ style" refuri="https://kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html"></target>
        </section>
        <section ids="example" names="example">
            <title>Example</title>
            <paragraph><strong>Indentation</strong></paragraph>
            <paragraph>Use a single tab for each indentation (8 characters).</paragraph>
            <literal_block force="False" highlight_args="{}" language="c" linenos="False" xml:space="preserve">if (mflags &amp; I2C_MSG_STOP) {
        ret = do_stop(dev, STOP_WAIT_COUNT);
}</literal_block>
            <paragraph><strong>Always use { }</strong></paragraph>
            <literal_block force="False" highlight_args="{}" language="c" linenos="False" xml:space="preserve">if (x is true) {
        we do y
}</literal_block>
            <literal_block force="False" highlight_args="{}" language="c" linenos="False" xml:space="preserve">switch (action) {
case KOBJ_ADD:
        return "add";
case KOBJ_REMOVE:
        return "remove";
case KOBJ_CHANGE:
        return "change";
default:
        return NULL;
}</literal_block>
            <paragraph><strong>CamelCase (AMD)</strong></paragraph>
            <paragraph>Used for variables, functions and file names</paragraph>
            <paragraph>Correct:</paragraph>
            <literal_block force="False" highlight_args="{}" language="c" linenos="False" xml:space="preserve">void SetSystemState(OSPM_Type newstate)
{

}</literal_block>
            <paragraph>Incorrect:</paragraph>
            <literal_block force="False" highlight_args="{}" language="c" linenos="False" xml:space="preserve">void setsystemstate(OSPM_Type newstate)
{

}</literal_block>
            <paragraph><strong>Copyright Statements (AMD)</strong></paragraph>
            <paragraph>Follow <reference name="Copyright Statements of Client BIOS process" refuri="https://confluence.amd.com/pages/viewpage.action?spaceKey=BIOSC&amp;title=Copyright+Statements">Copyright Statements of Client BIOS process</reference>.
                For 2022, the Copyright and License text has been reduced to a single line Copyright statement</paragraph>
            <target ids="copyright-statements-of-client-bios-process" names="copyright\ statements\ of\ client\ bios\ process" refuri="https://confluence.amd.com/pages/viewpage.action?spaceKey=BIOSC&amp;title=Copyright+Statements"></target>
            <paragraph>For new files</paragraph>
            <literal_block force="False" highlight_args="{}" language="c" linenos="False" xml:space="preserve">/*****************************************************************************
*
* Copyright (C) 2023 Advanced Micro Devices, Inc. All rights reserved.
*
******************************************************************************
*/</literal_block>
            <paragraph>For pre-existing file that is modified
                Include the first year in which the software was first developed and the last year it was substantively modified:</paragraph>
            <literal_block force="False" highlight_args="{}" language="c" linenos="False" xml:space="preserve">/******************************************************************************
Copyright (C) [insert range of years] Advanced Micro Devices, Inc. All rights reserved.
*****************************************************************************/</literal_block>
